               <msContents>
                  <summary>Psalter, ዳዊት፡</summary>
                <msItem xml:id="ms_i1"><locus from="1r" to="165r"/><title type="complete" ref="LIT2701Dawit"/>
                <textLang mainLang="gez">Gə‘əz</textLang>
              </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="Codex">
                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>
                           <watermark/>
                           <material key="parchment"/>
                        </support>
                        <extent>
                           <measure unit="leaf">ii + 167 </measure>
                           <dimensions type="outer" unit="mm">
                              <height>232</height>
                              <width>215</width>
                              <depth>90</depth>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>
                     </supportDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                  <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                  </seg>
                  <desc>The word God is not rubricated in the first three works; the word Mary is rubricated in the final two works</desc>
                  <desc>Columetric layout of text: <locus target="#127v"/> (Ps. 150); <locus target="#137r #137v"/> (tenth biblical canticle).</desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#ir(ecto)"/><desc> Crude drawing of a face above a ḥaräg</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#iv(erso)"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1066DavidHarp"/></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#29r"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1031VirginAndChild"/> attended by the angels <persName ref="PRS7049Michael"/> and <persName ref="PRS4377Gabriel"/></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4"><locus target="#59r"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1035HolyMan"/>,<persName ref="PRS4585Georgeo"/> and the <term key="dragon"/></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5"><locus target="#78v"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp ="AT1030Trinity"/> surrounded by the Four Living Creatures, with caption <q>“Holy trinity with four creatures.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6"><locus target="#98v"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp ="AT1049Resurrection"/> raising <persName ref="PRS1386Adam"/> and <persName ref="PRS3926Eve"/>, with caption <q>“Our Mother, Eve,” “How our Lord Jesus Christ rose from the dead on the third day,” and “with Adam.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d7"><locus target="#121r"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1005Crucifixion"/> with captions <q>“Saint John,” and “Crucifixion of Our Lord, Jesus Christ.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d8"><locus target="#147r"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1033Ascension"/> with caption <q>“The ascension of our Lord, Jesus Christ.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d9"><locus target="#160v"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1067LastSupper"/> with caption <q>“Maundy Thursday”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d10"><locus target="#167r"/><desc> Crude drawings of people</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d11">
                    Decorative designs:
                    <locus target="#1r #8r #16r #24r #34v #42v #49r #58r #70r #79r #85r #99r #111v #115r #121v #128v #141v #149r #150r"/> (haräg);
                    <locus target="#8r #16r #24r #34v #58r #64v #70r #99r #114v #121v #141v #148v #151v #157v #160r #165r"/> (line of alternating red and black dots);
                    <locus target="#84v #149v #158v #165r"/> (multiple full stops);
                    <locus target="#128r #148v"/> (multiple full stops and lines of alternating red and black dots)
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <locus target="#ir(ecto)"/>
                    <desc>
                    pentrial and ḥaräg
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <locus target="#iir(ecto)"> f. iir(ecto), top</locus>
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    Greeting Hymn to <persName ref="PRS1822IHA"/>, added later.
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰላም: ለመልክዕከ: መልክአ: ክቡር: ፍሡህ: ዘጥንተ: ፍጥረቱ: ነዋህ:
                    ኃይለ: ሥላሴ: መንክር: ውዱስ: ወስቡሕ:
                    እግዚአብሔር: ይቀብከ: ባሕታዊ: ንጹሕ:
                    ፍቁርየ: መሰልከኒ: ደመና: ብሩህ:</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <locus target="#iir(ecto)"> f. iir(ecto), middle</locus>
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    Greeting Hymn to Wälättä Wahǝd
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <locus target="#iir(ecto)"> f. iir(ecto), bottom</locus>
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    Greeting Hymn to (King) Wäldä Gäbrǝ’el
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a4">
                    <locus target="#iiv(erso)"> f. iiv(erso), first two lines</locus>
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    Excerpt from Praises of Mary
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a5">
                    <locus target="#iiv(erso)"> f. iiv(erso), left column, center</locus>
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    Excerpt from the Horologium: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ተፈሥሒ: ማርያም: ለአዳም: ፋሲካሁ:</foreign>
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ንዒ: ማርያም: ምስለ: ወልድኪ: መዋዒ:</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a6">
                    <locus target="#iiv(erso)"> f. iiv(erso), right column</locus>
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    Daily Prayers, “We Praise You, O Lord,” <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸሎት: ዘዘወትር:.</foreign>
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ነአኵተከ: እግዚኦ: (ወ)ንሴብሐከ: ንባርከከ: እግዚኦ:<gap reason="omitted"/></foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a7">
                    <locus target="#iiv(erso)"> f. iiv(erso), bottom three lines</locus>
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    Excerpt from one stanza of <title type="complete" ref="LIT1860Malkea"/>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a8">
                    <locus target="#165r #165v"> f. 165r, 165v, first 2 lines of column two</locus>
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    Layman’s Prayer, in Amharic.
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="am">ኖኅን: ከማየ: አይኅ: እስራኤልን: ከፈርዖን: ዳዊትን: ከሳኦል: ከኢሎፍሊ: ኤልያስን: ከኤልዛቤል: ሕዝቅያስን: ከሰናክሬም: ዳንኤል: ከአፈ: አናብስት: መርዶክዮስን: ከሐማ:<gap reason="omitted"/></foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a9">
                    <locus target="#165v"> f. 165v, col. 2, erased portion</locus>
                    <desc>
                    Curse on anyone who erases the text
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a10">
                    <locus target="#165v"> f. 165v, col. 2</locus>
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    Benediction. The last two lines is a continuation of the <title type="complete" ref="LIT1860Malkea"/>, see <locus target="#iiv(erso)"/>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a11">
                    <locus target="#166r"> f. 166r, col. 1, middle</locus>
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    Opening Prayer of the Daily Prayer, “In the Name of the Father, Son, and Holy Spirit”
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">በስመ አብ: ወወልድ<gap reason="omitted"/> በቅድስት: ስላሴ: እንዘ: አአምን: ወእት፡ መኃፀን: እክሕደከ: ሰይጣን:<gap reason="omitted"/></foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a12">
                    <locus target="#166r"> f. 166r, col. 1, lower</locus>
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    Excerpt from Horologium: <title type="complete" ref="LIT3118RepCh398"/>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a13">
                    <locus target="#166r"> f. 166r, col. 2, top</locus>
                    <desc>
                    Genealogical list of a family
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a14">
                    <locus target="#166r"> f. 166r, col. 2, lower</locus>
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    a second copy of the excerpt from the <title type="complete" ref="LIT1860Malkea"/>, see <locus target="#iiv(erso) #165v"> col. 2</locus>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a15">
                    <locus target="#166r"> f. 166r, col. 2, lower</locus>
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    Another copy of the Layman’s Prayer
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a16">
                    <locus target="#166v #167r"> f. 166v, 167r, col. 1, top</locus>
                    <desc>
                    Prediction of what happens if the beginning of the month falls on each of the days of the week (Sunday through Saturday). E.g. If Tuesday, devastation; if Friday, milk and honey; if Saturday, locusts devour, etc.
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez"><gap reason="omitted"/>ለእመ: ኮነ: በእሑድ: ባህር: ይመልዕ: ወቆር: ይከውን: ግንቦት: በልግ: ይከውን: እም፡ የማን: ይሄይስ: ነቢር: በፀጋም: ሞት: ህማም: ወቀጠና: ይበዝህ: ሲመት: ኢይጸንዕ:<gap reason="omitted"/></foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a17">
                    <locus from="167r"> f. 167r, col. 1, lower </locus><locus to="167v"></locus>
                    <desc>
                    Personal prayer, in a crude hand
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <locus target="#64v"/>
                    <desc>
                    A line written entirely in red ink and a series of two dotted lines with alternating black and red dots, mark the midpoint of the <title type="complete" ref="LIT2000Mazmur"/>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a18">
                    <locus target="#84v"/>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    Note of secondary ownership, Särṣä Maryam, his brother Ṣǝge Dәngәl, etc. ;Sege
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a19">
                    <locus target="#166r"> f. 166r, col. 1, top</locus>
                    <desc>
                    Note of ownership by Ḫǝsqǝyas and his son, Qalä Wäld
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <locus target="#167v"/>
                    <desc>
                    illegible text and pen trails
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <locus target="#ii #28 #58 #78 #98 #120 #146 #160"/>
                    <desc>
                    purple yarn is sewn into the fore edge to mark the location of illuminations as navigation system;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <locus target="#115"/>
                    <desc>
                    red yarn is sewn into the fore edge to mark content as navigation system
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a20">
                    <desc>
                    Psalm 118 contains the spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <locus target="#18v #19v #33v #34r #40v"/>
                    <desc>
                    (etc.) words of text are written interlinearly;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e7">
                    <locus target="#26v #40r #77r #102v #119r"/>
                    <desc>
                    (etc.) lines of text are written interlinearly;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e8">
                    <locus target="#22r #24r #28r #35r #38r"/>
                    <desc>
                    (etc.) text has been removed
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e9">
                    <locus target="#13r"/>
                    <desc>
                    The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above or below the end of the line (throughout). This scribe also will reduce the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
               </physDesc>
